subject: Best way to do "assertNotEquals()"?
msgSnippet: I must be missing something simple, but why is there no assertNotEquals() in JUnit?  There is assertNotSame() , but that s not quite the same thing.  I
messageBody:
I must be missing something simple, but why is there no
"assertNotEquals()" in JUnit? There is "assertNotSame()", but that's
not quite the same thing. I guess
"assertFalse(expected.equals(actual))" is about the best I can do.
